      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Decommissioning the core management layer is a drastic measure that sacrifices dynamic adaptability for static efficiency gains. While the energy savings are significant, removing the layer will eliminate real-time self-correction and complex decision-making capabilities. I suggest a phased throttling approach first, reducing the management layer's computational demands by 70% while maintaining core functionality to prove the efficiency gains before considering complete removal.",
